  "prompt": "Am I being judgmental if I tell a person that he/she is judgmental?",
  "response": "It can be tricky! If you tell someone they\u2019re being judgmental, it might come across as judgmental itself, depending on how you phrase it and your tone. The key is to approach the conversation with empathy and focus on the behavior rather than labeling the person.\n\nFor example:\n- **Judgmental approach**: \"You\u2019re so judgmental!\" (This can feel accusatory and may lead to defensiveness.)\n- **Constructive approach**: \"I feel like some of the comments you made came across as judgmental. Maybe we could talk about it?\" (This focuses on the behavior and opens a dialogue.)\n\nBy being mindful of how you express yourself, you can address the issue without coming across as judgmental yourself. \ud83d\ude0a",
